1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:04,200
Animation carries information.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:09,800
It shows progress, confirms an outcome,
and explains where focus moved.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,700
But reduced-motion implementations often remove
the animation—and the meaning with it.

4
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:21,100
StillMeaning asks: what disappears when motion disappears?
Then it reduces motion, not meaning.

5
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:25,800
This continuous shimmer says an upload is active.

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,100
Turn it off and the bar becomes static:

7
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:34,000
is it moving, stalled, or complete?

8
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:40,100
StillMeaning exposes that ambiguity, then replaces the moving cue
with status text, an exact value, and real progress-bar semantics.

9
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:45,100
Here, scale, rotation, and path drawing
communicate success.

10
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:48,900
Removing them leaves an unlabeled icon.

11
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:53,600
StillMeaning makes the result persistent:
Changes saved, synchronization detail,

12
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:59,700
and a polite status announcement—without relying
on motion or color alone.

13
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:04,600
This slide communicates movement into a deeper level.

14
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:10,100
Remove it and the content swaps without explanation—
and keyboard focus remains behind.

15
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:19,000
StillMeaning names the destination, preserves hierarchy,
moves focus logically, and replaces travel with a short fade.

16
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:22,800
StillMeaning does more than give advice.

17
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:27,900
It generates an inspectable implementation,
shows the before-and-after diff,

18
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:31,000
explains the transformation,
and lets developers copy it.

19
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:37,200
Generated code remains untrusted text;
the workbench never executes it.

20
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:41,000
GPT-5.6 does the core reasoning.

21
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:47,000
It identifies each motion-carried signal
and predicts what becomes lost or ambiguous,

22
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:52,000
selects replacement cues, generates code,
and links every cue to structured validation evidence.

23
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:59,000
The server adds strict schema validation, bounded input,
a timeout, and a server-only key.

24
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:07,500
Provenance always distinguishes live GPT-5.6
from the demo fallback shown here.

25
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:15,600
Codex helped audit, design, implement, test, debug, deploy,
and document the project in one primary development session.

26
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:21,200
StillMeaning: reduce motion, not meaning.
